introduce.description: Through reports, teams can comprehensively summarize all aspects of development activities, including progress, efficiency, quality, execution status, result analysis, etc. This helps improve transparency and communication, providing strong support for successful project delivery.

features.generateReport: Generate reports based on report templates at specified times and notify relevant personnel through events.
features.viewReport: View reports I added or reports authorized to me and their content.

globalAuth.title: Report Permission
globalAuth.description: Grant operation permissions for specified 'functions' to users, departments, and groups. 'View' permission is required when granting permissions. Users can only authorize functions they have permission to authorize.

content.contentHint: The following is the report output content directory information.

form.descriptionPlaceholder: Report description, use description to explain the content and purpose of this report, or add links to other resources, maximum 200 characters

progress.label: Project Progress Report
progress.description: Report project task, functional test, API test, scenario test four parts of completion progress.

testEvaluation.label: Test Evaluation Report
testEvaluation.description: Report test evaluation information, test evaluation results and detailed information.

sprint.label: Sprint Report
sprint.description: Report sprint information, development task completion progress, iteration and assignee summary statistics information.

task.label: Issue Report
task.description: Report the processing results and detailed information of a single issue.

plan.label: Test Plan Report
plan.description: Report test plan information, case test progress, test plan and test person summary statistics information.

case.label: Test Case Report
case.description: Report the test results and detailed information of a single test case.

services.label: Service Test Result Report
services.description: Report service information, summary statistics and API test results information under the service.

apis.label: API Test Result Report
apis.description: Report API information, functional test, performance test, stability test results.

result.label: Scenario Test Result Report
result.description: Report scenario information, functional test, performance test, stability test results.

functional.label: Functional Test Report
functional.description: Report the execution functional test sampling index detailed results.

performance.label: Performance Test Report
performance.description: Report the execution performance test sampling index detailed results.

stability.label: Stability Test Report
stability.description: Report the execution stability test sampling index detailed results.

customization.label: Customization Test Report
customization.description: Report the execution customization test sampling index detailed results.

contentTree.nodeTips: When there is an application node, the application node resource data is displayed, and when there is no application node, the execution node resource data is displayed. When there are multiple nodes, only the data of the first node is displayed.
contentTree.dispatchTips: When there are multiple nodes, only the log of the first execution node is displayed.
contentTree.samplingTips: When there are multiple nodes, only the log of the first execution node is displayed, and a maximum of 10000 lines of log information is supported.
